comments:
I feel like a looser, and I don't know how to get over it.

&#x200B;

A few years back in college, there was a girl I really liked (never felt for a girl like this before her or after), managed to ask her on a date, dated for a few months. Somehow I screwed it up, she said no and went out with another guy. Fast forward she just got married to that guy, **and joined my freaking company and the SAME FUCKING TEAM.** FUCK ME. JUST FUCK ME. I Hate it, I can't stand to see her laughing and smiling, I know its not her fault. Every time I think what could I possibly do different few years ago. My confidence is completely shattered. I can't even quit the job, because it's rare to get an equivalent job.

&#x200B;

I had to wish her the day she got married as the whole team wished her, one of the worst days in my life so far.

&#x200B;

Before people say go to gym to boost confidence, I literally do, I am very athletic and also do gym, I ran a marathon recently as well. It doesn't work, it doesn't help. I don't even know what to do, don't have any siblings, parents are really old. I don't think I even have the confidence to ask out any other girl anymore.

&#x200B;

Everyone said time will fix it, but time just makes it worse, I don't even find any other girls attractive anymore.  It's been 4 months since she joined and I feel like puking every time I see her laughing.

&#x200B;

Yaar me karo to kya karu....
